.mxm-executive-summary/sessions/tasks.md

# ── Local Python environment ─────────────────────────────────────────────
.conda/
__pycache__/
*.pyc

# ── Private documents subfolders — never committed (history purged) ───
# ADRs contain a mix of public governance narrative (tracked via negation
# rules below) and private architecture / security detail (default-ignored).
# build-artifacts-scripts, business (strategy, pack-moat, financials), and
# references contain internal tooling, strategy docs, and archival references.
# sales holds launch drafts, allocation models, and landing-design specs —
# all operator-local. Public-facing content stays tracked under
# documents/guides, documents/reference, documents/governance,
# documents/templates, documents/cross-surface, and documents/marketing.
documents/ADRs/*
documents/build-artifacts-scripts/
documents/business/
documents/references/
documents/sales/

# Legacy path alias (older commits used lowercase adr/)
documents/adr/

# Architecture docs (PRD, FRD, SRD, secrets) stay operator-local
documents/architecture/

# ── Public ADRs (negation exceptions) ─────────────────────────────────────
# The 7 ADRs below are public per the migration plan — they are moat
# narrative, governance contracts, pricing rationale, and payment choice.
# The remaining 4 ADRs (001 architecture baseline, 003 Worker license
# issuance, 005 IP protection 5-layer, 006 external content boundary)
# describe internal system architecture and stay private.
!documents/ADRs/README.md
!documents/ADRs/INDEX.md
!documents/ADRs/TEMPLATE.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-002-documents-as-executable-contracts.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-004-free-tier-executable-contract.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-007-behavioral-moat-framing-doctrine.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-008-community-pack-system.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-009-pack-architecture-l1-l2-l3.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-010-confidence-tag-technical-educator-rubric.md
!documents/ADRs/ADR-011-stripe-primary-payment-processor.md

# ── Maxim ledger state (session-local, never committed) ──────────────────
# documents/ledgers/ holds the canonical Executable Contract ledgers.
# Most are tracked (AGENT_SKILL_INVENTORY, MOAT_TRACKER, DEBUGGING_PLAYBOOK,
# BUG_TRACKER), but SESSION_CONTINUITY and SPRINT_CLI_INSTRUCTIONS are
# runtime session state — operator-local, never committed.
documents/ledgers/SESSION_CONTINUITY.md
documents/ledgers/SPRINT_CLI_INSTRUCTIONS.md

